<div class="faq-header">
  <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqd" data-type="collapse">
    <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
  <h2>What happens if a student is enrolled in courses and none of the professors have listed textbooks? Does the student still need to opt out of Wolverine Access?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqd">
      <br>
      <p>If there are no textbooks or course materials listed for any of the courses, students should not need to opt out of Wolverine Access. The textbook charge will not be applied to the student’s account. If students see a textbook charge for Wolverine Access on their account when no required textbooks or course materials are listed, please contact <a href="mailto:store@uvu.edu" style="color:#0e8345">store@uvu.edu</a>.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-header">
  <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqf" data-type="collapse">
    <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
  <h2>I am auditing a course; will I still be automatically opted-in and billed for Wolverine Access?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqf">
      <br>
      <p>Yes. All Wolverine Access costs, dates, and deadlines still apply.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-header">
  <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqg" data-type="collapse">
    <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
  <h2>How does Wolverine Access work for audited courses?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqg">
      <br>
      <p>Students who switch their courses to audit will have to be aware that they still need to opt out of Wolverine Access by the textbook drop deadline. Students who do not opt out of Wolverine Access by the textbook drop deadline will be billed to their account.</p>
</div>
</div>
<br>
<h2>PAYMENT INFORMATION</h2>

<div class="drop">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqG" data-type="collapse"><div class="faq-header">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
    <h2>How much does Wolverine Access cost?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqG">
      <br>
        <p>Wolverine Access is a flat-rate cost of $250 for each fall/spring semester and $150 for each summer semester, billed to your university account.</p>
        
  </div>
       
  <div class="faq-header">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqH" data-type="collapse">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
   <h2>When am I charged for Wolverine Access?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqH">
      <br>
      <p>The start-right Wolverine Access charge will appear on your university bill each semester. Payment for Wolverine Access follows all <a href="https://www.uvu.edu/tuition/undergraduate.html" target="_blank" style="color:#0e8345">tuition and fee payment deadlines and plans</a>. If you choose to opt-out of the program, the charge will be reversed on your account.
   </div>
    
     <div class="faq-header">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqy" data-type="collapse">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
   <h2>Why do affordable access programs automatically bill students unless they opt out?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqy">
      <br>
     <p>The opt-out structure ensures that campuses have the economies of scale necessary to secure bulk discounts from publishers and other suppliers. It also guarantees that students have their required materials automatically on or before the first day of classes. Students have two to three weeks before the opt-out deadline to shop, compare, and make sure they are getting their materials for the lowest price.</p>
 
    <p>When negotiating with publishers, institutions can achieve significant savings in an opt-out program and better terms, as it is operationally more efficient than an opt-in program, and that savings can be realized by institutions and students. On average, opt-out access programs save students an average of 59.4 percent compared to new print list prices (PLP) and 30.8 percent from digital list prices (DLP).</p>
   </div>
   
   
    
    
  <div class="faq-header">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqI" data-type="collapse">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
    <h2>Does financial aid apply to Wolverine Access?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqI">
      <br>
      <p>Financial aid may apply to Wolverine Access. To learn more, please contact <a href="https://www.uvu.edu/financialaid/" target="_blank" style="color:#0e8345">UVU Financial Aid</a>.</p>

 </div>
</div>
<br>
<h2>COURSE ENROLLMENT</h2> <!--new section-->
<div class="drop">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqJ" data-type="collapse"><div class="faq-header">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
    <h2>How do I get my textbooks if I add or drop a course?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqJ">
      <br>
        <p><strong>Adding a Course:</strong> Any required eBooks for the added course will become available to you in Textbooks & Course Materials in Canvas within 3-5 days. If printed books are required for your new course, you will receive an email from the UVU Store when they are ready for pickup. This information can also be found on the Textbooks & Course Materials tab in Canvas.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Dropping a Course:</strong> Any required eBooks will be removed from your Textbooks & Course Materials. If printed books were required for the class you dropped, you must return those books to the UVU Store by February 3, 2025. Non-returned print materials will be charged to your university account at the publisher's listed new book price.</p>
        
  </div>
       
  <div class="faq-header">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqK" data-type="collapse">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
   <h2>I am waitlisted for a course; will I have access to the program materials?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqK">
      <br>
      <p>No, only courses for which you are officially registered will be available as part of your Wolverine Access start-right program.</p>
   </div>
    
    
  <div class="faq-header">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqL" data-type="collapse">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
    <h2>Will I receive a refund if I drop a course?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqL">
      <br>
      <p>Yes, if you drop a course before the drop deadline, the cost associated with the course materials for that class will be refunded. However, no refunds are given after the deadline has passed.</p>

      </div>
      
        <div class="faq-header">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqM" data-type="collapse">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
    <h2>What happens if I change classes after the semester starts?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqM">
      <br>
      <p>If you change classes within the same credit load before the drop deadline, your course materials will automatically update in Canvas, and you won’t incur additional charges.</p>

      </div>
        <div class="faq-header">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqN" data-type="collapse">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
    <h2>What if I prefer physical textbooks over digital ones?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqN">
      <br>
      <p>Most materials are delivered digitally and can be accessed through Canvas on any device. While the program primarily provides digital versions of textbooks, you can request physical copies at the UVU Store for an additional fee, depending on availability and timelines, or you can source the materials on your own.</p>

      </div>
        <div class="faq-header">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqP" data-type="collapse">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
    <h2>My course requires a physical textbook, and I live out of state. How do I get my physical textbook?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqP">
      <br>
      <p>Please email <a href="mailto:store.uvu.edu" style="color:#0e8345">store@uvu.edu</a>. An additional course materials shipping fee may apply.</p>

      </div>
        <div class="faq-header">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqQ" data-type="collapse">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
    <h2>How do I access digital textbooks?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqQ">
      <br>
      <p>Digital textbooks are integrated into your Canvas courses. Simply log in to Canvas, navigate to your course, and find your materials under the Modules or Textbooks & Course Materials section.</p>

      </div>
        <div class="faq-header">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqR" data-type="collapse">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
    <h2>What if I experience technical issues with my digital materials?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqR">
      <br>
      <p>If you have trouble accessing your digital textbooks, contact the UVU Store or the IT help desk. They can assist with troubleshooting and ensure you have access to your materials.</p>

      </div>
      
         <div class="faq-header">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqS" data-type="collapse">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
    <h2>Can I keep my digital textbooks after the semester ends?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqS">
      <br>
      <p>Access to digital materials varies by publisher. Some materials may only be available for the duration of the semester, while others might remain accessible for a longer period. Check the terms of each digital textbook within Canvas.</p>

      </div>
      
              <div class="faq-header">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqb" data-type="collapse">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
   <h2>Are course packets included in the Wolverine Access $250 fee?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqb">
      <br>
     <p>Yes, when you opt in to Wolverine Access, your first course packet in each course is included in the $250 fee. Any additional course packets beyond the initial set must be purchased separately at the UVU Store for the regular retail price.</p>
   </div>
   
    <div class="faq-header">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqc" data-type="collapse">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
   <h2>What happens when a professor requires an older or outdated edition of the textbook?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqc">
      <br>
     <p>If the publisher no longer provides digital access to the older edition, the professor may reach out to the publisher to request the older version be made available. If this is possible, the professor is required to reach out to the UVU Store at <a href="mailto:textbookadoptions@uvu.edu" style="color:#0e8345">textbookadoptions@uvu.edu</a> to make sure it’s included in Wolverine Access.</p>
   </div>
   
    <div class="faq-header">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqe" data-type="collapse">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
   <h2>What happens if the professor lists textbooks and course materials late and I’m not seeing them in Wolverine Access?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqe">
      <br>
     <p>Discuss the timing of the textbook adoptions with your professor.</p>
     
     <p>If you see a textbook listed on your syllabus that you do not see on your Wolverine Access booklist, please inform your professor to contact the UVU Store. Timely and accurate textbook adoptions or book requests are the instructor’s responsibility. We cannot guarantee that late textbook adoptions or book requests will be available through Wolverine Access.</p>
   </div>
      
        <div class="faq-header">
    <a href="#" class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#faqh" data-type="collapse">
      <i class="facets-faceted-navigation-item-color-facet-group-expander-icon"></i>
   <h2>If a professor elects a digital-only format for textbooks, who supplies textbooks to meet student accommodations?</h2>
    </a>
    </div>
    <div class="collapse inner-text" id="faqh">
      <br>
     <p>Students requiring alternative textbook formats must be approved for an 'alternative text accommodation' through the UVU Accessibility Services Office. Once that accommodation is approved, the Accessible Technology Center will have several resources for obtaining or creating the required alternative format. Contact Accessibility Services or the Accessible Technology Center with further questions.</p>
     
     <p><u><a href="https://www.uvu.edu/accessibility-services/" target="_blank" style="color:#000">Contact UVU Accessibility Services at</a></u><a href="mailto:accessibilityservices@uvu.edu" style="color:#0e8345"> accessibilityservices@uvu.edu</a>.</p>
          <p><u><a href="https://www.uvu.edu/accessibletech/" target="_blank" style="color:#000">Contact UVU Accessible Tech at</a></u><a href="mailto:accessibletech@uvu.edu" style="color:#0e8345"> accessibletech@uvu.edu</a>.</p>
          
